                WHY ORGANIC?
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="title-head">
            <div class="header-copy">
                <p>
                Well, first, because it's in our name. Organic products are not just boutique characteristics of high-end food and agricultural products, they offer much, nuch more. We initially made these confections for our family and didn't want foods laced with any unknown combination of fungicides, pesticides, herbicides, hormones, or antibiotics, and we don't think you would wnat that either.
            </p>

            </div>
        </div>

       <div class="form-container">
            <div class="form-title">
                Organic foods reduce persistent chemicals and pesticides.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="title-head">
            <div class="header-copy">
            <p>
               Buying organic food promotes a less toxic environment for all living things.
            </p>

            </div>
        </div>

         <div class="form-container">
            <div class="form-title">
                By making our products organic, we avoid rGBH, GMOs, and sub-therapeutic antibiotics.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="title-head">
            <div class="header-copy">
            <p>
              These food technologies have been rushed to market with little to no long-term testing. Should our children be the guinea pigs for these tests? Most European countries ban most of these practices outright.
            </p>

            </div>
        </div>


         <div class="form-container">
            <div class="form-title">
                We reduce, if not eliminate, off-farm pollution.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="title-head">
            <div class="header-copy">
            <p>
              The chemicals that grow our crops and feed our cattle don't just go away, they flow downstream. Genetically modified seeds can be blown across fileds, cross-pollinating other crops. Industrial farming waste pollutes communities and creates river and ocean dead zones.
            </p>

            </div>
        </div>

